{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dac9c854-e838-4cea-a40a-5e1d2a776c37","content":"In .NET 10, `dotnet test` runs on Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default** — no opt-in needed. You can safely remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property; it was only required in .NET 9 to bridge `dotnet test` to MTP.\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013jDv1rpsKfDyzQePiBv8u5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2deda3292eae4a62ac9098b8494b8f06/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2deda3292eae4a62ac9098b8494b8f06/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"d4d40ea5-e5f3-4015-940b-99729f2af84c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about MTP (Microsoft.Testing.Platform) support. Let me provide accurate guidance.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively (it's the default). The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed — it was a bridge property for .NET 9 to opt in to MTP support via `dotnet test`. In .NET 10, this is the default behavior.\n\nLet me confirm this understanding and advise removing the property.","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"3404:371ABE:72FDA40:7F5CC25:69F3FB7E"},"id":"1ba208cf-8599-4fec-9879-7193d0a183d6","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:01:57.969Z","parentId":"7ccaaa5e-a4ff-410d-940d-2ec5b2307def"}
